Dataset ds001_depmap: 50000 cell lines, 36 non-outcome features, 10 dependency outcomes.
I used only the local task bundle. Because the sandbox blocked the requested uv-managed Python interpreter, I parsed dataset.parquet directly in Node and ran Welch mean comparisons plus systematic single-predicate and pairwise subgroup/interaction screens.

Overall strongest patterns:
- dependency_BRAF: best single predicate was `braf_v600e` equals 1, mean -0.8047 vs -0.2495 (effect -0.5552, p=<1e-300). Best pair was `braf_v600e` equals 1 AND `brca2_loss` equals 1, mean -0.8350 vs -0.3083 (effect -0.5267, interaction -0.0351, interaction p=0.1169).
- dependency_EGFR: best single predicate was `egfr_amplification` equals 1, mean -0.6010 vs -0.2524 (effect -0.3486, p=<1e-300). Best pair was `egfr_amplification` equals 1 AND `lineage_subtype` is "basal", mean -0.6610 vs -0.2785 (effect -0.3825, interaction -0.0546, interaction p=0.0970).
- dependency_ERBB2: best single predicate was `erbb2_amplification` equals 1, mean -0.6856 vs -0.2535 (effect -0.4321, p=<1e-300). Best pair was `erbb2_amplification` equals 1 AND `lineage_subtype` is "her2_enriched", mean -0.7525 vs -0.2944 (effect -0.4581, interaction -0.0671, interaction p=0.0372).
- dependency_KRAS: best single predicate was `kras_mutation` equals 1, mean -0.5594 vs -0.2520 (effect -0.3075, p=<1e-300). Best pair was `kras_mutation` equals 1 AND `growth_rate_doublings_per_day` is high (>= 0.964), mean -0.5898 vs -0.3081 (effect -0.2817, interaction 1.851e-4, interaction p=0.9826).
- dependency_RIT1: best single predicate was `nf1_loss` equals 1, mean -0.3527 vs -0.2572 (effect -0.0955, p=<1e-300). Best pair was `nf1_loss` equals 1 AND `lineage` is "brain", mean -0.4047 vs -0.2650 (effect -0.1397, interaction -0.0582, interaction p=0.0056).
- dependency_KIF18A: best single predicate was `lineage` is "colorectal", mean -0.7204 vs -0.2524 (effect -0.4680, p=<1e-300). Best pair was `lineage` is "colorectal" AND `apc_mutation` equals 1, mean -0.9425 vs -0.2527 (effect -0.6899, interaction -0.6822, interaction p=<1e-300).
- dependency_TMED10: best single predicate was `growth_rate_doublings_per_day` is high (>= 0.964), mean -0.2816 vs -0.2447 (effect -0.0369, p=<1e-300). Best pair was `culture_type` is "semi_adherent" AND `lineage` is "prostate", mean -0.3028 vs -0.2537 (effect -0.0491, interaction -0.0493, interaction p=0.0302).
- dependency_DHX9: best single predicate was `growth_rate_doublings_per_day` is high (>= 0.964), mean -0.3614 vs -0.3243 (effect -0.0371, p=<1e-300). Best pair was `rnaseq_MYC_log2_tpm` is high (>= 5.669) AND `lineage_subtype` is "squamous", mean -0.3985 vs -0.3329 (effect -0.0656, interaction -0.0522, interaction p=0.0022).
- dependency_POLR2A: best single predicate was `growth_rate_doublings_per_day` is high (>= 0.964), mean -0.4972 vs -0.3928 (effect -0.1043, p=<1e-300). Best pair was `growth_rate_doublings_per_day` is high (>= 0.964) AND `lineage_subtype` is "adenocarcinoma", mean -0.5189 vs -0.4162 (effect -0.1026, interaction -0.0161, interaction p=0.1637).
