  Result for h15: Best single DHX9 predicate was `growth_rate_doublings_per_day` is high (>= 0.964): mean dependency_DHX9 -0.3614 (n=12577) versus -0.3243 otherwise; effect=-0.0371, p=<1e-300.
  Result for h16: Top DHX9 subgroup screen result: `lineage_subtype` is "her2_enriched" AND `erbb2_amplification` equals 1 had mean dependency_DHX9 -0.4052 (n=142) versus -0.3335 otherwise; subgroup effect=-0.0718, interaction=-0.0750, interaction p=0.0194.
Iteration 9:
  Hypothesis h17: Cell lines where `growth_rate_doublings_per_day` is high (>= 0.964) have more negative `dependency_POLR2A` scores than other cell lines.
  Hypothesis h18: POLR2A dependency is strongest in cell lines where `growth_rate_doublings_per_day` is high (>= 0.964) and `lineage_subtype` is "her2_enriched"; this subgroup has more negative `dependency_POLR2A` than other cell lines.
  Result for h17: Best single POLR2A predicate was `growth_rate_doublings_per_day` is high (>= 0.964): mean dependency_POLR2A -0.4972 (n=12577) versus -0.3928 otherwise; effect=-0.1043, p=<1e-300.
  Result for h18: Top POLR2A subgroup screen result: `growth_rate_doublings_per_day` is high (>= 0.964) AND `lineage_subtype` is "her2_enriched" had mean dependency_POLR2A -0.5358 (n=252) versus -0.4185 otherwise; subgroup effect=-0.1174, interaction=-0.0551, interaction p=0.0327.
Iteration 10:
  Hypothesis h19: Cell lines where `myc_amplification` equals 1 have more negative `dependency_RPL11` scores than other cell lines.
  Hypothesis h20: RPL11 dependency is strongest in cell lines where `myc_amplification` equals 1 and `growth_rate_doublings_per_day` is high (>= 0.964); this subgroup has more negative `dependency_RPL11` than other cell lines.
  Result for h19: Best single RPL11 predicate was `myc_amplification` equals 1: mean dependency_RPL11 -0.3614 (n=8055) versus -0.2523 otherwise; effect=-0.1091, p=<1e-300.
  Result for h20: Top RPL11 subgroup screen result: `myc_amplification` equals 1 AND `growth_rate_doublings_per_day` is high (>= 0.964) had mean dependency_RPL11 -0.3936 (n=2557) versus -0.2632 otherwise; subgroup effect=-0.1303, interaction=-0.0140, interaction p=0.1358.

Conclusions:
Classical oncogene dependencies were strongly supported: BRAF dependency tracked braf_v600e, EGFR dependency tracked egfr_amplification, ERBB2 dependency tracked erbb2_amplification, and KRAS dependency tracked kras_mutation. The pairwise screens sharpened some of these into lineage or subtype contexts, although not every pair had a statistically significant interaction term beyond the strong single-driver effect.
Other dependencies showed distinct contexts in the final subgroup screen: dependency_RIT1 in `nf1_loss` equals 1 AND `lineage` is "brain"; dependency_KIF18A in `lineage` is "colorectal" AND `apc_mutation` equals 1; dependency_TMED10 in `lineage_subtype` is "luminal" AND `stk11_loss` equals 1; dependency_DHX9 in `lineage_subtype` is "her2_enriched" AND `erbb2_amplification` equals 1; dependency_POLR2A in `growth_rate_doublings_per_day` is high (>= 0.964) AND `lineage_subtype` is "her2_enriched"; dependency_RPL11 in `myc_amplification` equals 1 AND `growth_rate_doublings_per_day` is high (>= 0.964). The best-supported effects are the signed subgroup differences reported above; weak starting ideas that were not supported were not retained as final conclusions.
All dependency outcomes received at least one systematic heterogeneity screen; all final refined subgroup hypotheses state the complete pair of predicates selected by that screen.


